title: Released dozbc, TGMDroid, and clock widget.
message:
Released dozbc, TGMDroid, and clock widget.

New icons, package name, lots of changes.  v1.0 on dozbc,
TGMDroid, and DozclockWidget.  Still developing on
DozCalendar.

title: Redid TGMDroid, clock, and dozbc icons.
message: Redid TGMDroid, clock, and dozbc icons.

title: Greatly improved error handling.
message:
Greatly improved error handling.

Still need to include error handling for times.

title: Added date validation in AddnewActivity.
message: Added date validation in AddnewActivity.

title: Settings handling is much improved.
message:
Settings handling is much improved.

Now deletes previous settings when they are changed.  Can't
do this in a separate thread, though, because I'm not sure
how to check when that thread's done, and it was writing at
strange places in the file because of it.  Must resolve that
issue.

title: Added in moon phases.
message:
Added in moon phases.

Thing is, they only show up on dates when something else is
already set.  May need to think of a better way to display
them.

title: Now the first_dow variable actually does work.
message:
Now the first_dow variable actually does work.

Array out of bounds error coming up occasionally, apparently
from the sort function.  Not sure why, and it's not
deliberately reproducible so far.  I can't find any array in
the sort function, so I'm mystified.

title: Worked on reading the options from the data file.
message:
Worked on reading the options from the data file.

Still can't put the options in the data file, nor am I
entirely sure how I'll get the moon phases in at all.  But
progress!  Also, cleaned up the weekly display so that it
will properly show different first_dow.

title: Started the settings activity.
message:
Started the settings activity.

Also finally made Datelib.print return dozenal dates,
formatted according to the customizable date format.  Small
thing, but obviously important.

title: Moved data handling into separate thread.
message: Moved data handling into separate thread.

title: Nicened up the UI for adding new activities.
message: Nicened up the UI for adding new activities.

title: Added intermittent date handlers!
message:
Added intermittent date handlers!

Yes, all of them!  Remarkably simple!  Also correct a stupid
mistake:  printing the ArrayList of Datelibs tried for a -1
index on the first shot; this caused a crash when you asked
for the date or date range containing the first record.
Corrected this pretty easily.

title: *Huge* improvements to DozCalendar.
message:
*Huge* improvements to DozCalendar.

Because DozCalendar didn't exist until this commit!
DozcalDroid is now DozCalendar, though it still comes up as
DozcalDroid on the actual device, because that's the way I
did it.  Nearly complete rewrite.

title: Removed keystore foolishly included before.
message:
Removed keystore foolishly included before.

Of course, am now compiling with new keystore in eclipse.

title: Huge initial commit to the repository; call it v0.X.
message:
Huge initial commit to the repository; call it v0.X.

Been developing these for some time without using git, just
using eclipse's inbuilt version control; making this commit
to allow committing the code to github.  Mostly functional;
a few tweaks to add here and there.

1.)  DozcalDroid crashes when adding intermittent event in
every month of the year; however, the event is successfully
added.
2.)  Should add ability to select arbitrary characters for X
and E; as it is, you can enter them as * or # or X or E or a
or b, but they all output as X and E.
3.)  Others.
